            <div class="col-md-12">
                <p>
                    I am astrophysics PhD student at the Institute of Astronomy in the University of Cambridge. My work lies in the intersection of Galactic dynamics and binary star evolution. Since the first Gaia data release I have focussed on applying Bayesian inference to this overlap. I will be applying for post-doctoral positions in the 2017/18 cycle.
                </p>
            </div>
